{
  "doc_id": "40503",
  "text": "Last but not least, it should be noted that all security-related approaches to anomaly detection, including our own one, are susceptible to mimicry attacks [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , in which an attacker tries to execute behavior that is malicious, but nevertheless mimics legal behavior in such a way that the malicious behavior remains undetected. This problem can be mitigated somewhat by keeping the application model undisclosed, but to the best of our knowledge no way to absolutely avert mimicry attacks is known to date.",
